articles.author: Al Jazeera
articles.title: Powerful 6.8-magnitude earthquake rattles Morocco, north Africa - Al Jazeera English
articles.description: The earthquake struck late Friday evening, with the epicentre 75 kilometres west of Marrekesh, a major economic centre.
articles.content:
A powerful 6.8 magnitude earthquake has shocked Morocco, sending pulses from the city of Rabat in the north to Sidi Ifni in the south and beyond.
